cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with few-shot learning in image classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating few-shot learning algorithms, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
